1232  LinkageLocation location = buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(0);

1234  location.IsRegister() && !location.IsAnyRegister();
1235  InstructionOperand op;
1236  // If earlier phases specified a particular register, don't override
1237  // their choice.
1238  if (location_is_fixed_register) {
1239  op = g.UseLocation(callee, location);
1240  } else if (call_use_fixed_target_reg) {
1241  op = g.UseFixed(callee, kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1242  } else {
1243  op = g.UseRegister(callee);
1244  }
1245  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(op);
1246  break;
1247  }
1248  case CallDescriptor::kCallJSFunction:
1249  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(
1250  g.UseLocation(callee, buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(0)));
1251  break;
1252  }
1253  DCHECK_EQ(1u, buffer->instruction_args.size());
1254 
1255  // If the call needs a frame state, we insert the state information as
1256  // follows (n is the number of value inputs to the frame state):
1257  // arg 1 : deoptimization id.
1258  // arg 2 - arg (n + 2) : value inputs to the frame state.
1259  size_t frame_state_entries = 0;
1260  USE(frame_state_entries); // frame_state_entries is only used for debug.
1261  if (buffer->frame_state_descriptor != nullptr) {
1262  OpIndex frame_state = frame_state_opt.value();
1263 
1264  // If it was a syntactic tail call we need to drop the current frame and
1265  // all the frames on top of it that are either inlined extra arguments
1266  // or a tail caller frame.
1267  if (is_tail_call) {
1268  frame_state = Cast<FrameStateOp>(frame_state).parent_frame_state();
1269  buffer->frame_state_descriptor =
1270  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->outer_state();
1271  while (buffer->frame_state_descriptor != nullptr &&
1272  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->type() ==
1273  FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
1274  frame_state = Cast<FrameStateOp>(frame_state).parent_frame_state();
1275  buffer->frame_state_descriptor =
1276  buffer->frame_state_descriptor->outer_state();
1277  }
1278  }
1279 
1280  int const state_id = sequence()->AddDeoptimizationEntry(
1281  buffer->frame_state_descriptor, deopt_kind, DeoptimizeReason::kUnknown,
1282  node.id(), FeedbackSource());
1283  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(g.TempImmediate(state_id));
1284 
1285  StateObjectDeduplicator deduplicator(instruction_zone());
1286 
1287  frame_state_entries =
1288  1 + AddInputsToFrameStateDescriptor(
1289  buffer->frame_state_descriptor, frame_state, &g, &deduplicator,
1290  &buffer->instruction_args, FrameStateInputKind::kStackSlot,
1291  instruction_zone());
1292 
1293  DCHECK_EQ(1 + frame_state_entries, buffer->instruction_args.size());
1294  }
1295 
1296  size_t input_count = buffer->input_count();
1297 
1298  // Split the arguments into pushed_nodes and instruction_args. Pushed
1299  // arguments require an explicit push instruction before the call and do
1300  // not appear as arguments to the call. Everything else ends up
1301  // as an InstructionOperand argument to the call.
1302  auto iter(arguments.begin());
1303  size_t pushed_count = 0;
1304  for (size_t index = 1; index < input_count; ++iter, ++index) {
1305  DCHECK_NE(iter, arguments.end());
1306 
1307  LinkageLocation location = buffer->descriptor->GetInputLocation(index);
1308  if (is_tail_call) {
1309  location = LinkageLocation::ConvertToTailCallerLocation(
1310  location, stack_param_delta);
1311  }
1312  InstructionOperand op = g.UseLocation(*iter, location);
1313  UnallocatedOperand unallocated = UnallocatedOperand::cast(op);
1314  if (unallocated.HasFixedSlotPolicy() && !is_tail_call) {
1315  int stack_index = buffer->descriptor->GetStackIndexFromSlot(
1316  unallocated.fixed_slot_index());
1317  // This can insert empty slots before stack_index and will insert enough
1318  // slots after stack_index to store the parameter.
1319  if (static_cast<size_t>(stack_index) >= buffer->pushed_nodes.size()) {
1320  int num_slots = location.GetSizeInPointers();
1321  buffer->pushed_nodes.resize(stack_index + num_slots);
1322  }
1323  PushParameter param = {*iter, location};
1324  buffer->pushed_nodes[stack_index] = param;
1325  pushed_count++;
1326  } else {
1327  if (location.IsNullRegister()) {
1328  EmitMoveFPRToParam(&op, location);
1329  }
1330  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(op);
1331  }
1332  }
1333  DCHECK_EQ(input_count, buffer->instruction_args.size() + pushed_count -
1334  frame_state_entries);
1335  USE(pushed_count);
1336  if (V8_TARGET_ARCH_STORES_RETURN_ADDRESS_ON_STACK && is_tail_call &&
1337  stack_param_delta != 0) {
1338  // For tail calls that change the size of their parameter list and keep
1339  // their return address on the stack, move the return address to just above
1340  // the parameters.
1341  LinkageLocation saved_return_location =
1342  LinkageLocation::ForSavedCallerReturnAddress();
1343  InstructionOperand return_address =
1344  g.UsePointerLocation(LinkageLocation::ConvertToTailCallerLocation(
1345  saved_return_location, stack_param_delta),
1346  saved_return_location);
1347  buffer->instruction_args.push_back(return_address);
1348  }
1349 }

2442  {
2443  // The DeoptimizeIf/Branch condition is not a projection.
2444  const ProjectionOp* projection = TryCast<ProjectionOp>(maybe_projection);
2445  if (!projection) return;
2446 
2447  if (projection->index != 1u) {
2448  // The DeoptimizeIf/Branch isn't on the Projection[1]
2449  // (ie, not on the overflow bit of a BinopOverflow).
2450  return;
2451  }
2452 
2453  DCHECK_EQ(projection->input_count, 1);
2454  OpIndex node = projection->input();
2455  if (block(schedule_, node) != current_block_) {
2456  // The projection input is not in the current block, so it shouldn't be
2457  // emitted now, so we don't need to eagerly schedule its Projection[0].
2458  return;
2459  }
2460 
2461  auto* binop = TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node);
2462  auto* unop = TryCast<OverflowCheckedUnaryOp>(node);
2463  if (binop == nullptr && unop == nullptr) return;
2464  if (binop) {
2465  DCHECK(binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd ||
2466  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub ||
2467  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul);
2468  } else {
2469  DCHECK_EQ(unop->kind, OverflowCheckedUnaryOp::Kind::kAbs);
2470  }
2471 
2472  OptionalOpIndex result = FindProjection(node, 0);
2473  if (!result.valid() || IsDefined(result.value())) {
2474  // No Projection(0), or it's already defined.
2475  return;
2476  }
2477 
2478  if (block(schedule_, result.value()) != current_block_) {
2479  // {result} wasn't planned to be scheduled in {current_block_}. To
2480  // avoid adding checks to see if it can still be scheduled now, we
2481  // just bail out.
2482  return;
2483  }
2484 
2485  // Checking if all uses of {result} that are in the current block have
2486  // already been Defined.
2487  // We also ignore Phi uses: if {result} is used in a Phi in the block in
2488  // which it is defined, this means that this block is a loop header, and
2489  // {result} back into it through the back edge. In this case, it's
2490  // normal to schedule {result} before the Phi that uses it.
2491  for (OpIndex use : turboshaft_uses(result.value())) {
2492  // We ignore TupleOp uses, since TupleOp don't lead to emitted machine
2493  // instructions and are just Turboshaft "meta operations".
2494  if (!Is<TupleOp>(use) && !IsDefined(use) &&
2495  block(schedule_, use) == current_block_ && !Is<PhiOp>(use)) {
2496  return;
2497  }
2498  }
2499 
2500  // Visiting the projection now. Note that this relies on the fact that
2501  // VisitProjection doesn't Emit something: if it did, then we could be
2502  // Emitting something after a Branch, which is invalid (Branch can only
2503  // be at the end of a block, and the end of a block must always be a
2504  // block terminator). (remember that we emit operation in reverse order,
2505  // so because we are doing TryPrepareScheduleFirstProjection before
2506  // actually emitting the Branch, it would be after in the final
2507  // instruction sequence, not before)
2508  VisitProjection(result.value());
2509 }

2820  case ChangeOp::Kind::kZeroExtend:
2821  DCHECK_EQ(change.from, Rep::Word32());
2822  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Word64());
2823  return VisitChangeUint32ToUint64(node);
2824  case ChangeOp::Kind::kSignExtend:
2825  DCHECK_EQ(change.from, Rep::Word32());
2826  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Word64());
2827  return VisitChangeInt32ToInt64(node);
2828  case ChangeOp::Kind::kTruncate:
2829  DCHECK_EQ(change.from, Rep::Word64());
2830  DCHECK_EQ(change.to, Rep::Word32());
2831  MarkAsWord32(node);
2832  return VisitTruncateInt64ToInt32(node);
2833  case ChangeOp::Kind::kBitcast:
2834  switch (multi(change.from, change.to)) {
2835  case multi(Rep::Word32(), Rep::Word64()):
2836  return VisitBitcastWord32ToWord64(node);
2837  case multi(Rep::Word32(), Rep::Float32()):
2838  return VisitBitcastInt32ToFloat32(node);
2839  case multi(Rep::Word64(), Rep::Float64()):
2840  return VisitBitcastInt64ToFloat64(node);
2841  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word32()):
2842  return VisitBitcastFloat32ToInt32(node);
2843  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64()):
2844  return VisitBitcastFloat64ToInt64(node);
2845  default:
2846  UNREACHABLE();
2847  }
2848  }
2849  UNREACHABLE();
2850  }
2851  case Opcode::kTryChange: {
2852  const TryChangeOp& try_change = op.Cast<TryChangeOp>();
2853  MarkAsRepresentation(try_change.to.machine_representation(), node);
2854  DCHECK(try_change.kind ==
2855  TryChangeOp::Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowUndefined ||
2856  try_change.kind ==
2857  TryChangeOp::Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowUndefined);
2858  const bool is_signed =
2859  try_change.kind ==
2860  TryChangeOp::Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowUndefined;
2861  switch (multi(try_change.from, try_change.to, is_signed)) {
2862  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), true):
2863  return VisitTryTruncateFloat64ToInt64(node);
2864  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word64(), false):
2865  return VisitTryTruncateFloat64ToUint64(node);
2866  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), true):
2867  return VisitTryTruncateFloat64ToInt32(node);
2868  case multi(Rep::Float64(), Rep::Word32(), false):
2869  return VisitTryTruncateFloat64ToUint32(node);
2870  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word64(), true):
2871  return VisitTryTruncateFloat32ToInt64(node);
2872  case multi(Rep::Float32(), Rep::Word64(), false):
2873  return VisitTryTruncateFloat32ToUint64(node);
2874  default:
2875  UNREACHABLE();
2876  }
2877  UNREACHABLE();
2878  }
2879  case Opcode::kConstant: {
2880  const ConstantOp& constant = op.Cast<ConstantOp>();
2881  switch (constant.kind) {
2882  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32:
2883  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64:
2884  case ConstantOp::Kind::kSmi:
2885  case ConstantOp::Kind::kTaggedIndex:
2886  case ConstantOp::Kind::kExternal:
2887  break;
2888  case ConstantOp::Kind::kFloat32:
2889  MarkAsFloat32(node);
2890  break;
2891  case ConstantOp::Kind::kFloat64:
2892  MarkAsFloat64(node);
2893  break;
2894  case ConstantOp::Kind::kHeapObject:
2895  case ConstantOp::Kind::kTrustedHeapObject:
2896  MarkAsTagged(node);
2897  break;
2898  case ConstantOp::Kind::kCompressedHeapObject:
2899  MarkAsCompressed(node);
2900  break;
2901  case ConstantOp::Kind::kNumber:
2902  if (!IsSmiDouble(constant.number().get_scalar())) MarkAsTagged(node);
2903  break;
2904  case ConstantOp::Kind::kRelocatableWasmCall:
2905  case ConstantOp::Kind::kRelocatableWasmStubCall:
2906  case ConstantOp::Kind::kRelocatableWasmCanonicalSignatureId:
2907  case ConstantOp::Kind::kRelocatableWasmIndirectCallTarget:
2908  break;
2909  }
2910  VisitConstant(node);
2911  break;
2912  }

2937  case WordUnaryOp::Kind::kCountLeadingZeros:
2938  return VisitWord64Clz(node);

2941  case WordUnaryOp::Kind::kPopCount:

2999  case WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub:

3208  }
3209  case Opcode::kShift: {
3210  const auto& shift = op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
3211  if (shift.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {

3213  switch (shift.kind) {
3214  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros:
3215  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:
3216  return VisitWord32Sar(node);
3217  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
3218  return VisitWord32Shr(node);

3220  return VisitWord32Shl(node);

3222  return VisitWord32Ror(node);

3231  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:

3233  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical:

3235  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:

3239  case ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateLeft:
3240  return VisitWord64Rol(node);
3241  }

3244  }
3245  case Opcode::kCall:
3246  // Process the call at `DidntThrow`, when we know if exceptions are caught
3247  // or not.
3248  break;
3249  case Opcode::kDidntThrow:
3250  if (current_block_->begin() == node) {
3251  DCHECK_EQ(current_block_->PredecessorCount(), 1);
3252  DCHECK(current_block_->LastPredecessor()
3253  ->LastOperation(*this->turboshaft_graph())
3254  .Is<CheckExceptionOp>());
3255  // In this case, the Call has been generated at the `CheckException`
3256  // already.
3257  } else {
3258  VisitCall(op.Cast<DidntThrowOp>().throwing_operation());
3259  }
3260  EmitIdentity(node);
3261  break;
3262  case Opcode::kFrameConstant: {
3263  const auto& constant = op.Cast<FrameConstantOp>();
3264  using Kind = FrameConstantOp::Kind;
3265  OperandGenerator g(this);
3266  switch (constant.kind) {
3267  case Kind::kStackCheckOffset:
3268  Emit(kArchStackCheckOffset, g.DefineAsRegister(node));
3269  break;
3270  case Kind::kFramePointer:
3271  Emit(kArchFramePointer, g.DefineAsRegister(node));
3272  break;
3273  case Kind::kParentFramePointer:
3274  Emit(kArchParentFramePointer, g.DefineAsRegister(node));
3275  break;
3276  }
3277  break;
3278  }
3279  case Opcode::kStackPointerGreaterThan:
3280  return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(node);
3281  case Opcode::kComparison: {
3282  const ComparisonOp& comparison = op.Cast<ComparisonOp>();
3283  using Kind = ComparisonOp::Kind;
3284  switch (multi(comparison.kind, comparison.rep)) {
3285  case multi(Kind::kEqual, Rep::Word32()):
3286  return VisitWord32Equal(node);
3287  case multi(Kind::kEqual, Rep::Word64()):
3288  return VisitWord64Equal(node);
3289  case multi(Kind::kEqual, Rep::Float32()):
3290  return VisitFloat32Equal(node);
3291  case multi(Kind::kEqual, Rep::Float64()):
3292  return VisitFloat64Equal(node);
3293  case multi(Kind::kEqual, Rep::Tagged()):
3294  if constexpr (Is64() && !COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
3295  return VisitWord64Equal(node);
3296  }
3297  return VisitWord32Equal(node);
3298  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThan, Rep::Word32()):
3299  return VisitInt32LessThan(node);
3300  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThan, Rep::Word64()):
3301  return VisitInt64LessThan(node);
3302  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThan, Rep::Float32()):
3303  return VisitFloat32LessThan(node);
3304  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThan, Rep::Float64()):
3305  return VisitFloat64LessThan(node);
3306  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Word32()):
3307  return VisitInt32LessThanOrEqual(node);
3308  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Word64()):
3309  return VisitInt64LessThanOrEqual(node);
3310  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Float32()):
3311  return VisitFloat32LessThanOrEqual(node);
3312  case multi(Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Float64()):
3313  return VisitFloat64LessThanOrEqual(node);
3314  case multi(Kind::kUnsignedLessThan, Rep::Word32()):
3315  return VisitUint32LessThan(node);
3316  case multi(Kind::kUnsignedLessThan, Rep::Word64()):
3317  return VisitUint64LessThan(node);
3318  case multi(Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Word32()):
3319  return VisitUint32LessThanOrEqual(node);
3320  case multi(Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual, Rep::Word64()):
3321  return VisitUint64LessThanOrEqual(node);
3322  default:
3323  UNREACHABLE();
3324  }
3325  UNREACHABLE();
3326  }
3327  case Opcode::kLoad: {
3328  const LoadOp& load = op.Cast<LoadOp>();
3329  MachineType loaded_type = load.machine_type();
3330  MarkAsRepresentation(loaded_type.representation(), node);
3331  if (load.kind.maybe_unaligned) {
3332  DCHECK(!load.kind.with_trap_handler);
3333  DCHECK(!load.kind.is_atomic);
3334  if (loaded_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3335  InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()
3336  .IsUnalignedLoadSupported(loaded_type.representation())) {
3337  return VisitLoad(node);
3338  } else {
3339  return VisitUnalignedLoad(node);
3340  }
3341  } else if (load.kind.is_atomic) {
3342  if (load.result_rep == Rep::Word32()) {
3343  return VisitWord32AtomicLoad(node);
3344  } else if (load.result_rep == Rep::Word64()) {
3345  return VisitWord64AtomicLoad(node);
3346  } else if (load.result_rep == Rep::Tagged()) {
3347  return kTaggedSize == 4 ? VisitWord32AtomicLoad(node)
3348  : VisitWord64AtomicLoad(node);
3349  }
3350  } else if (load.kind.with_trap_handler) {
3351  DCHECK(!load.kind.maybe_unaligned);
3352  return VisitProtectedLoad(node);
3353  } else {
3354  return VisitLoad(node);
3355  }
3356  UNREACHABLE();
3357  }
3358  case Opcode::kStore: {
3359  const StoreOp& store = op.Cast<StoreOp>();
3360  MachineRepresentation rep =
3361  store.stored_rep.ToMachineType().representation();
3362  if (store.kind.maybe_unaligned) {
3363  DCHECK(!store.kind.with_trap_handler);
3364  DCHECK_EQ(store.write_barrier, WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier);
3365  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 ||
3366  InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements()
3367  .IsUnalignedStoreSupported(rep)) {
3368  return VisitStore(node);
3369  } else {
3370  return VisitUnalignedStore(node);
3371  }
3372  } else if (store.kind.is_atomic) {
3373  if (store.stored_rep.SizeInBytes() == 8) {
3374  return VisitWord64AtomicStore(node);
3375  } else {
3376  DCHECK_LE(store.stored_rep.SizeInBytes(), 4);
3377  return VisitWord32AtomicStore(node);
3378  }
3379  } else if (store.kind.with_trap_handler) {
3380  DCHECK(!store.kind.maybe_unaligned);
3381  return VisitProtectedStore(node);
3382  } else {
3383  return VisitStore(node);
3384  }
3385  UNREACHABLE();
3386  }
3387  case Opcode::kTaggedBitcast: {
3388  const TaggedBitcastOp& cast = op.Cast<TaggedBitcastOp>();
3389  switch (multi(cast.from, cast.to)) {
3390  case multi(Rep::Tagged(), Rep::Word32()):
3391  MarkAsWord32(node);
3392  if constexpr (Is64()) {
3393  DCHECK_EQ(cast.kind, TaggedBitcastOp::Kind::kSmi);
3394  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
3395  return VisitBitcastSmiToWord(node);
3396  } else {
3397  return VisitBitcastTaggedToWord(node);
3398  }
3399  case multi(Rep::Tagged(), Rep::Word64()):
3400  MarkAsWord64(node);
3401  return VisitBitcastTaggedToWord(node);
3402  case multi(Rep::Word32(), Rep::Tagged()):
3403  case multi(Rep::Word64(), Rep::Tagged()):
3404  if (cast.kind == TaggedBitcastOp::Kind::kSmi) {
3405  MarkAsRepresentation(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned, node);
3406  return EmitIdentity(node);
3407  } else {
3408  MarkAsTagged(node);
3409  return VisitBitcastWordToTagged(node);
3410  }
3411  case multi(Rep::Compressed(), Rep::Word32()):
3412  MarkAsWord32(node);
3413  if (cast.kind == TaggedBitcastOp::Kind::kSmi) {
3414  return VisitBitcastSmiToWord(node);
3415  } else {
3416  return VisitBitcastTaggedToWord(node);
3417  }
3418  default:
3419  UNIMPLEMENTED();
3420  }
3421  }
3422  case Opcode::kPhi:
3423  MarkAsRepresentation(op.Cast<PhiOp>().rep, node);
3424  return VisitPhi(node);
3425  case Opcode::kProjection:
3426  return VisitProjection(node);
3427  case Opcode::kDeoptimizeIf:
3428  return VisitDeoptimizeIf(node);
3429 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3430  case Opcode::kTrapIf:
3431  return VisitTrapIf(node);
3432 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3433  case Opcode::kCatchBlockBegin:
3434  MarkAsTagged(node);
3435  return VisitIfException(node);
3436  case Opcode::kRetain:
3437  return VisitRetain(node);
3438  case Opcode::kOsrValue:
3439  MarkAsTagged(node);
3440  return VisitOsrValue(node);
3441  case Opcode::kStackSlot:
3442  return VisitStackSlot(node);
3443  case Opcode::kFrameState:
3444  // FrameState is covered as part of calls.
3445  UNREACHABLE();
3446  case Opcode::kLoadRootRegister:
3447  return VisitLoadRootRegister(node);
3448  case Opcode::kAssumeMap:
3449  // AssumeMap is used as a hint for optimization phases but does not
3450  // produce any code.
3451  return;
3452  case Opcode::kDebugBreak:
3453  return VisitDebugBreak(node);
3454  case Opcode::kAbortCSADcheck:
3455  return VisitAbortCSADcheck(node);
3456  case Opcode::kSelect: {
3457  const SelectOp& select = op.Cast<SelectOp>();
3458  // If there is a Select, then it should only be one that is supported by
3459  // the machine, and it should be meant to be implementation with cmove.
3460  DCHECK_EQ(select.implem, SelectOp::Implementation::kCMove);
3461  MarkAsRepresentation(select.rep, node);
3462  return VisitSelect(node);
3463  }
3464  case Opcode::kWord32PairBinop: {
3465  const Word32PairBinopOp& binop = op.Cast<Word32PairBinopOp>();
3466  MarkAsWord32(node);
3467  MarkPairProjectionsAsWord32(node);
3468  switch (binop.kind) {
3469  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kAdd:
3470  return VisitInt32PairAdd(node);
3471  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kSub:
3472  return VisitInt32PairSub(node);
3473  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kMul:
3474  return VisitInt32PairMul(node);
3475  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:
3476  return VisitWord32PairShl(node);
3477  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
3478  return VisitWord32PairShr(node);
3479  case Word32PairBinopOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic:
3480  return VisitWord32PairSar(node);
3481  }
3482  UNREACHABLE();
3483  }
3484  case Opcode::kAtomicWord32Pair: {
3485  const AtomicWord32PairOp& atomic_op = op.Cast<AtomicWord32PairOp>();
3486  if (atomic_op.kind != AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kStore) {
3487  MarkAsWord32(node);
3488  MarkPairProjectionsAsWord32(node);
3489  }
3490  switch (atomic_op.kind) {
3491  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kAdd:
3492  return VisitWord32AtomicPairAdd(node);
3493  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kAnd:
3494  return VisitWord32AtomicPairAnd(node);
3495  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kCompareExchange:
3496  return VisitWord32AtomicPairCompareExchange(node);
3497  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kExchange:
3498  return VisitWord32AtomicPairExchange(node);
3499  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kLoad:
3500  return VisitWord32AtomicPairLoad(node);
3501  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kOr:
3502  return VisitWord32AtomicPairOr(node);
3503  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kSub:
3504  return VisitWord32AtomicPairSub(node);
3505  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kXor:
3506  return VisitWord32AtomicPairXor(node);
3507  case AtomicWord32PairOp::Kind::kStore:
3508  return VisitWord32AtomicPairStore(node);
3509  }
3510  }

3512  return MarkAsFloat64(node), VisitBitcastWord32PairToFloat64(node);
3513  case Opcode::kAtomicRMW: {
3514  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = op.Cast<AtomicRMWOp>();
3515  MarkAsRepresentation(atomic_op.memory_rep.ToRegisterRepresentation(),
3516  node);
3517  if (atomic_op.in_out_rep == Rep::Word32()) {
3518  switch (atomic_op.bin_op) {
3519  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAdd:
3520  return VisitWord32AtomicAdd(node);
3521  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kSub:
3522  return VisitWord32AtomicSub(node);
3523  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAnd:
3524  return VisitWord32AtomicAnd(node);
3525  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kOr:
3526  return VisitWord32AtomicOr(node);
3527  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kXor:
3528  return VisitWord32AtomicXor(node);
3529  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kExchange:
3530  return VisitWord32AtomicExchange(node);
3531  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange:
3532  return VisitWord32AtomicCompareExchange(node);
3533  }
3534  } else if (atomic_op.in_out_rep == Rep::Word64()) {
3535  switch (atomic_op.bin_op) {
3536  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAdd:
3537  return VisitWord64AtomicAdd(node);
3538  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kSub:
3539  return VisitWord64AtomicSub(node);
3540  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kAnd:
3541  return VisitWord64AtomicAnd(node);
3542  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kOr:
3543  return VisitWord64AtomicOr(node);
3544  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kXor:
3545  return VisitWord64AtomicXor(node);
3546  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kExchange:
3547  return VisitWord64AtomicExchange(node);
3548  case AtomicRMWOp::BinOp::kCompareExchange:
3549  return VisitWord64AtomicCompareExchange(node);
